GCL Poly Rises to Three-Year High on Profit in Hong Kong Premarket Trading

-- B y   M a r c o   L u i
-- 
2011-03-18T01:24:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/gcl-poly-rises-to-three-year-high-on-profit-in-hong-kong-premarket-trading.html
  GCL-Poly Energy Holdings Ltd. (3800) ,  China ’s largest polysilicon maker, surged to the highest in
three years in Hong Kong premarket trading after reporting net
income that beat estimates.  The stock climbed 9.1 percent to HK$4.30, the highest level
since November 2007, on the city’s stock exchange.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Lui at 
 mlui11@bloomberg.net  